tive, indem er interkulturelle Kommunikation als Dispositiv begreift. Dies gewährt neue Einblicke in unterschiedliche Festschreibungen vermeintlicher Wirkweisen von Kultur auf soziales Handeln. Auf Grundlagen der Ethnomethodologie wird so ein dispositivtheoretisch informierter Rahmen für eine zukünftige Erforschung interkultureller Kommunikation entwickelt.  aFrom the perspective of cultural studies, intercultural communication as a research subject has long since experienced a crisis of theory but has, at the same time, grown in social relevance. Dominic Busch reads the current research from a new perspective by understanding intercultural communication as a dispositive. This provides new insight into different descriptions of reputed cultural mode of action on social behavior. Busch presents an ethnomethodologically developed, dispositive-theory informed framework for future study of intercultural communication.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aDispositiv. 4aEthnomethodologie. 4aForschungsüberblick. 4aInterkulturalität. 4aKultur. 4aKultursoziologie. 4aMembership Categorization Analysis. 4aSoziologie. 4aWissenschaft. 4aWissenschaftssoziologie. 4aWissenssoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aInterculturalism.  aScience.  aSociology of Culture.  aSociology of Knowledge.  aSociology of Science.  aSociology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2010-2013z9783110352856oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Sozialw. 2010-2013z9783110370713oZDB-23-TSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2013z9783110401219oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839425558zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyt